@page
@model RoleplayersGuild.Site.Directory.Welcome.IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Welcome to the Guild!";
    // FIXED: Changed to the single-column layout.
    Layout = "~/Site.Directory/Shared/_Layout1Col.cshtml";
}

@* REMOVED: The unnecessary and incorrect "LeftCol" section has been removed. *@

<div class="alert alert-success" role="alert">
    <h2 class="alert-heading">Welcome to RPG!</h2>
    <p>Welcome and thank you for joining the Role-Players Guild! As you may already know, RPG is built from the ground up to cater to the needs and desires of the RP community. This isn't just some forum site or social media tool that is used for RP, it is a website made specifically for RP.</p>
    <p>As a member of RPG, you are now part of our beautiful and growing family. Please make sure you are respectful to all the other members and if anyone is disrespectful to you, please let us know <strong>right away</strong>.</p>
    <hr>
    <p>With that, it's time for you to join us! You can now create your very first character and start exploring the site!</p>

    <div class="mt-4">
        <a asp-page="/User-Panel/My-Characters/Create" class="btn btn-primary">Create Your First Character</a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4">
        <p class="mb-0">Thank you,</p>
        <p class="mb-0">The RPG Staff</p>
    </div>
</div>